@node DESCRIPTION "CanonToolBox · Description"
Description
===========
  CanonToolBox is a tool to play with digicams from Canon via USB/PTP.
@endnode

@node FEATURES "CanonToolBox · Features"
Features
========
  - Full control over the remote functionality
  - Taking pictures as .jpg
  - Taking videos of unlimited length as .yuv
  - Setting of all known device properties
  - Multithreaded design
  - Advanced Log-system
  - Simple ARexx-support
@endnode

@node REQUIREMENTS "CanonToolBox · Requirements"
Requirements
============
  - AmigaOS 3.x / MorphosOS v1.x
  - Poseidon USB-Stack
  - NList classes
  - MUI 3.8

  - PTP compatible CANON-Digital-Camera
@endnode

@node INSTALL "CanonToolBox · Installation"
Installation
============
  Installation is very simple.

  Just drag the CanonToolBox-drawer where you like.
  CanonToolBox don't need assigns.
@endnode

@node USAGE "CanonToolBox · Usage"
Usage
=====
  GUI
  ---
  Using CanonToolBox is very simple.

  @{b}Basic-rule:@{ub}
  First turn you camera on, and _then_ start CanonToolBox!
  First quit 'CanonToolBox', and _then_ turn you camera off!

  Most should be self-explaining...

  The log-window is opened via the menuitem 'Log/Show...'

  'Wait for Camera-Button'
  If this checkmark is enabled, the caputre-routine waits till
  you press the shoot-button on the camera.

  To disable the FPS-counter in the display,
  toggle the menuitem 'Remote/ShowFPS'


  ARexx
  -----
  TakeShoot PICTURE/A


  Thats all ;)
@endnode

